.TH CREPLACE 3L LOCAL

.SH NAME
creplace - replace a character in a string

.SH SYNOPSIS
.ft B
char *
.br
creplace(str, old, new)
.br
char *str, old, new;
.ft P

.SH DESCRIPTION
Replaces every occurrence of the old character \fIold\fP with
the new character \fInew\fP in the string \fIstr\fP.
Returns \fIstr\fP.

.SH FILES
creplace.c

.SH SEE ALSO
squish(3L)
